I've been a lurker on SeoMoz for roughly six months now. Patiently soaking up the vast amount of information, advices, and tips passing through these pages. Without divulging into too many cliched superlatives, I owe somewhat of debt of gratitude to SeoMoz, and Hubspot - two of the defining sites in the sphere of SEO and Inbound Marketing. 

I learnt the value of blogging to promote our company website, which was duly launched. Not merely for the sake of blogging, but to actually add some value to the audience. But with taking this bold step, one could quickly undermine it, by committing simple grammar or writing style mistakes. The importance of this too, was learnt from these two sites. Naturally, within a few months traffic to our domain had increased substantially 